Case called at 10:38 AM.
Defendant Dustin Jon Olson in court with attorney Jane Ellen Bucher.   Katherine Findley appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
State informs the court this matter is resolved.
Defendant enters a plea of "NO CONTEST" to Counts 1 & 2.
Attorney Bucher files plea and waiver of rights form.
Court questions defendant RE: plea and waiver of rights, court also questions attorney Bucher RE: her clients plea and waiver of rights.
Court finds plea is made freely, knowingly & voluntarily.
Court accepts plea and finds the defendant "GUILTY" to Counts 1 & 2
Court finds that there is a factual basis.
State moves for joint recommendation of the parties.
Attorney Bucher concurs with the state.
-Sentence with held 2 years probation w/conditions.
-Dismissing Count 3 Per/Agreement
COURT: Grants motion of the parties 
Sentence withheld probation for a period of 2 years with conditions.
DNA Surcharge imposed on count 2 only.
Domestic Abuse Surcharge imposed on Count 1 .
